The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the behavior of polygonal chains in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a likely sub-category. The problem involves combinatorial aspects, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves simulations and experiments, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
